-- Rain to Fall in China’s Drought-Parched Yunnan, Forecaster Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-03-02T14:34:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/rain-to-fall-in-china-s-drought-parched-yunnan-forecaster-says.html
China ’s drought-affected
southwestern province of Yunnan will get as much as 16
millimeters of rain between tonight and March 4, the National
Meteorological Center said on its website.  The drought that started in December has parched 15
prefectures and municipalities, limiting drinking water for 3.19
million people and 1.58 million head of livestock, Xinhua News
Agency reported, citing the provincial government.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
William Bi in Beijing at 
